data.chText: （通常界限不明的）地区，区域，地方
data.enText: a large area of land, usually without exact limits or borders

data.chText: 北美人口最为稠密的地区之一
data.enText: one of the most densely populated regions of North America
one of the areas that a country is divided into, that has its own customs and/or its own government

data.chText: （一国除首都以外的）全部地区，所有区域
data.enText: all of a country except the capital city

data.chText: （通常指有某种特性或问题的）身体部位
data.enText: a part of the body, usually one that has a particular character or problem

data.chText: （表示不确切的数字等）大约，差不多
data.enText: used when you are giving a number, price, etc. to show that it is not exact
He earns somewhere in the region of €50 000.

means: (一国除首都以外的)全部地区

ex.chText: 商业区/停车区/住宅区
ex.enText: a commercial/parking/residential zone

ex.chText: 危险区/安全区
ex.enText: a danger/safety zone

ex.chText: 地震带
ex.enText: earthquake zones

ex.chText: 他们正把部队调离战区。
ex.enText: They are pulling their troops out of the battle zone.

ex.chText: 中国的大部分地区处于温带。
ex.enText: Most of China is in the temperate zone.

synonyms.bx: 指具有某种区别性特征而被划分出来的区域、地带；用作科技术语时，多指地球上依据温度划分的气候带。

ex.chText: 在澳大利亚还有大片地区至今荒无人烟。
ex.enText: There're large areas in Australia still unpopulated.

ex.chText: 此处禁止停车。
ex.enText: Parking is prohibited in this area.

ex.chText: 我们将在旅馆接待处碰面。
ex.enText: We will meet in the hotel reception area.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指国家、市镇等的区域，或建筑、处所等中作特定用途的场地。

ex.chText: 玉米/森林/绿色地带
ex.enText: the corn/forest/green belt

ex.chText: 《圣经》地带（指美国南部新教教义极具影响的地区）
ex.enText: the Bible Belt

ex.chText: 防护林带能减弱风力。
ex.enText: The shelter belt breaks the force of the wind.

synonyms.bx: 指具有某种特色或某类人居住的地区或地带。

ex.chText: 你知道这个地区的邮政编码吗？
ex.enText: Do you know the postal code of this district?

ex.chText: 北京最热闹的商业区是王府井大街一带。
ex.enText: The busiest shopping district in Beijing is around Wangfujing Street.

synonyms.bx: 多指由政府等机构出于行政管理等目的而明确划分的地区。

ex.chText: 伦敦及（英国）其他各地区
ex.enText: London and the regions

ex.chText: 这些植物生长在阿尔卑斯山区。
ex.enText: These plants grow in the Alpine region.

ex.chText: 山区居民的生活比过去幸福多了。
ex.enText: The inhabitants of mountainous regions live more happily than ever before.

ex.chText: 我去过西班牙的巴斯克区。
ex.enText: I have visited the Basque region of Spain.

synonyms.bx: 通常指界线不明的较大地区或一国的行政分区；the regions 则指某国除首都以外的所有区域。

ex.chText: 我的家乡位于一片美丽的土地上。
ex.enText: My hometown is located on a beautiful stretch of land.

ex.chText: 这一河段少有船只经过。
ex.enText: Ships are rarely seen on this stretch of the river.

ex.chText: 除了近在眼前的一小段路之外，她什么也看不见。
ex.enText: She could see nothing but a small stretch of road just ahead.

synonyms.bx: 尤指长而窄的一片地域或水域。

data.chText: （表示不确切的数字等）大约，差不多
data.enText: used when you are giving a number, price, etc. to show that it is not exact
He earns somewhere in the region of €50 000.

tr: a part of an animal that has a special function or is supplied by a given artery or nerve
a knowledge domain that you are interested in or are communicating about
example: it was a limited realm of discourse
here we enter the region of opinion

tr: the extended spatial location of something
example: religions in all parts of the world

tr: a large indefinite location on the surface of the Earth
the approximate amount of something (usually used prepositionally as in `in the region of')
example: it was going to take in the region of two or three months to finish the job
the price is in the neighborhood of $100

value.def: A region is a large area of land that is different from other areas of land, for example because it is one of the different parts of a country with its own customs and characteristics, or because it has a particular geographical feature.

example.ex: ...Barcelona, capital of the autonomous region of Catalonia.
example.tran: 加泰罗尼亚自治区首府巴塞罗那

value.def: The regions are the parts of a country that are not the capital city and its surrounding area.

example.ex: Tax incentives would be used to attract firms to the regions, away from the South-East.
example.tran: 将采取税收优惠政策把公司吸引到东南部以外的各地区。

value.def: You can refer to a part of your body as a region.
You say in the region of to indicate that an amount that you are stating is approximate.

example.ex: The scheme will cost in the region of six million pounds.
example.tran: 这个计划将耗资大约600万英镑。
